  "text": "The carcinogenesis pathway seems to be associated to the host-bacteria interaction, with changes in the intestinal stem cell function. The chronic inflammation process and secondary and hyper proliferation of the intestinal stem cells initiate malignant modifications, maintenance and metastases. Carcinoids and lymphomas affect mainly the ileum in a proportion of 87% and 60%, respectively. A study from Canada showed that adenocarcinomas occur in the ileum in 16% [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
